<h2>What Is GEO for Local Businesses?</h2>
<p>GEO for local businesses is the application of <a href="/blog/what-is-geo/">generative engine optimization</a> specifically to local search queries. The goal is getting AI engines to mention, recommend, and cite your business when users ask location-based questions.</p>
<p>Traditional local SEO targets the Google local pack. Local GEO targets the AI-generated answers that increasingly appear above the local pack (AI Overviews) or replace it entirely (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Gemini).</p>
<p>The difference: Google shows a list and lets the user choose. AI engines choose for the user. When ChatGPT recommends 3 plumbers in your city, the 4th plumber does not exist in that interaction.</p>
<p><strong>Key point:</strong> Local GEO determines whether AI engines pick your business when someone in your city asks for a recommendation.</p>
<h2>Why GEO Matters for Local Businesses</h2>
<p>The shift from "search and choose" to "ask and receive" changes local business visibility at a fundamental level.</p>
<p><strong>Rapid consumer adoption.</strong> 45% of consumers now use AI for local service discovery. The growth rate from 6% to 45% in 12 months shows this is not a niche behavior. It is becoming the default.</p>
<p><strong>Extremely limited visibility.</strong> Only 1.2% of local businesses appear in ChatGPT recommendations. Only 15.2% appear in Gemini. The competition for AI visibility is lower now than it will be in 12 months. Early movers capture the recommendation slots before competitors optimize.</p>
<p><strong>Higher intent, fewer options.</strong> AI presents 2-3 recommendations per query. Traditional Google search shows 10+ results plus ads. In AI search, being outside the top 3 means zero visibility. There is no "page 2" equivalent.</p>
<p><strong>Reviews become selection criteria.</strong> AI engines use reviews as a quality filter. Businesses recommended by ChatGPT <a href="https://searchengineland.com/ai-local-visibility-report-2026-468085">average 4.3 stars</a>. On Gemini, the average is 3.9 stars. Low review scores disqualify businesses from AI recommendations entirely.</p>
<p><strong>The bottom line:</strong> Local businesses that do not optimize for AI search will lose customers to the 1-2% of competitors that do.</p>
