<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Does ChatGPT recommend local businesses?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. When users ask ChatGPT for local service recommendations, it pulls from Bing results, Yelp, TripAdvisor, and other directory data to recommend 2-3 businesses. Currently, only 1.2% of local businesses appear in ChatGPT recommendations. The number is growing as more users shift to AI for local discovery.</p>
<p><strong>How do I get my business recommended by AI search engines?</strong></p>
<p>Focus on 3 areas: complete and accurate <a href="/blog/optimize-google-business-profile/">Google Business Profile</a> with regular posts and photo updates, consistent directory listings across 5+ platforms (especially Yelp and industry-specific directories), and fresh reviews with a 4.0+ star rating. Implement LocalBusiness schema on your website and create location-specific content.</p>
<p><strong>Is local GEO different from regular GEO?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Regular GEO focuses on getting cited in AI responses for informational queries. Local GEO specifically targets location-based recommendations where AI picks 2-3 businesses from a geographic area. Local GEO depends more heavily on directory data, reviews, NAP consistency, and Google Business Profile completeness than regular GEO.</p>
<p><strong>What star rating do I need for AI recommendations?</strong></p>
<p>ChatGPT-recommended businesses average 4.3 stars. Gemini averages 3.9 stars. Perplexity averages 4.1 stars. A minimum of 4.0 stars with consistent recent reviews gives you the best chance of appearing in AI local recommendations across all platforms.</p>
<p>AI search is changing which local businesses get found first. The shift from user-driven choice to AI-driven recommendation means fewer businesses get seen. The ones that optimize for local GEO now will own the recommendation slots as AI adoption continues to grow.</p>
